deck: Comics penciler, inker and colorist from Rosario, Santa Fe in Argentina.
description:
Kristian Rossi, from Rosario, Sante Fe in Argentina, began drawing at the age of 9, mainly dedicated to traditional art inspired by American comic artists along with Japanese anime and manga artists. With the advent of new digital trends, Kristian entered the process of digital art and taught himself to work with Photoshop and Anime Studio Pro.

Starting in 2005, he began to dabble in the art of animation, mainly in the 2D digital art as an animator and with traditional 2D art as an assistant animator and inbetweener. Kristian eventually worked on several animated films for the cinema and several animated television series.

From 2012-2013 he was the penciler and inker on the crime-fiction comic book Chambers from Arcana Studio with writer Wes Locher.
name: Kristian Rossi

deck: Wes Locher is the writer of the sci-fi/comedy series UNIT 44 (Alterna, 2015), the heist graphic novel THE UNDOUBTABLES (Markosia Enterprises, 2014), the crime-fiction miniseries CHAMBERS (Arcana Studio, 2013) and has contributed shorts for anthologies published by Titan Comics and GrayHaven Comics.
description:
Wes Locher got his start in comics in 2012 with the short story, London Shadow, drawn by Allen Byrns and published in the MegaBook anthology from CE publishing. From there, he contributed short stories to five volumes of The Gathering from GrayHaven Comics and in 2013 released the crime-fiction miniseries, Chambers, with Arcana Studio. The book featured art by Kristian Rossi and colors by Kefas Armando.

In 2014 Wes released the heist graphic novel The Undoubtables with artist and co-creator, Emre Ozdamarlar. The book, featuring interior colors by Kefas Armando and cover colors by Kell Smith, was published by Markosia Enterprises.

Wes debuted his next miniseries, the sci-fi/comedy Unit 44 through publisher Alterna Comics. The book, drawn and co-created by artist Eduardo Jimenez, was released monthly as a digital-first initiative to the ComiXology platform in March - June 2015.

June 2015 also saw the release of Wes' short comic Adrift, co-created with artist Alex Diotto. The 4-page comedy short was published in the Lost in Space anthology by Titan Comics in partnership with Britain's Lakes International Comic Art Festival. The anthology, available for free exclusively on the ComiXology platform, was the culmination of 2014's Titan Comics Undiscovered Talent Competition.

In 2016, Wes released three one-shot comic books through indie publisher Primary Target Press, including the dystopian comedy Hipsters Vs. Rednecks with artist Tyler Kelting, the sci-fi/time travel thriller The Temporal with artist Kristian Rossi and the M.C. Escher-inspired sci-fi tale Maintenance with artist Stan Chou.
name: Wes Locher
